data.text: Gather the necessary parts needed for the build.
Take the shaft component and insert the concaved end into the top clamp, securing it in place using the grub screw
Insert the top of the shaft through the cylinder
position the top clamp inside the gap in one of the side rails. Aligning the cylinder with the top screw hole of the siderail
Secure the cylinder to the side rail using a panhead screw
Lay the build on the side rail and position the bottom clamp in the bottom hole of the side rail.
Take the other side rail and align it with the other side of the cylinder, top clamp and bottom clamp. Secure with a panhead screw to the cylinder. Attach the handle to the top of the shaft.
Take the left and right aluminum angles and position them where the bottom clamp aligns with the holes on the parts.
place the front wall in the gaps towards the front of the aluminum angles
Secure the Aluminum Angles to the baseplate using 2 panhead screws though the helos on the bottom of the aluminum angles and into the 2 screw holes in the scenter of the baseplate
